[CODEX] session 2026-02-28:
Context:
User requested a cleaner, API-inline style for lua/highlights.lua and disliked the previous direction that routed most behavior through layered apply_* helper functions.

Rationale:
I flattened the structure to a single apply_highlight_overrides pass containing direct nvim_set_hl calls for all stable overrides (LSP inactive groups and markdown links). This keeps the data flow visible in one place and removes the previous call-chain orchestration.

Design boundary:
Two tiny helpers remain: one to read existing highlight definitions (needed for defensive fallbacks and copying) and one to apply no-underline clones. These are retained because they depend on runtime colorscheme data and cannot be represented as static literals without behavior loss.

Evidence:
- Headless require(highlights) succeeds.
- hlexists(CustomDiagText)=1, hlexists(CustomDiagLine)=1, and markdown inline target group exists after load.
- ColorScheme autocmd still re-applies through the single flattened override pass.
